notesStmt.note: Title from caption title (f. 1r); spine title Instruction pour les offic. d'artillerie.

msContents.summary: Treatise on artillery and explosives, as well as the construction of devices necessary for the construction and use of artillery and explosives. Concludes with several tables concerning distances and a detailed table of contents. A note in pencil on the last flyleaf refers to M. Robert, officier dans la marine; calculations in pencil inside lower cover; 2 notes in French with military references laid inside lower cover, one a note to Sergent Moulin, perhaps signed M. A. Gravitz.

msItem.title: Instruction pour les officiers de l'artillerie

support.watermark: ANTOINE MALME[?], enclosed in a rectangle with rounded ends, with a quatrefoil separating the words; bird enclosed in a circle.

supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 425 leaves; 1-235,235-366, [i], 367-525, 525-684, 684-803, [804-846 (838-846 blank)]; pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: Contemporary (18th-century) calf, gilt spine with title.

origin.p: Written in France after 1720 (latest date in text, p. 369).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by D. L. Béatrix du Tronquet, officier de l'artillerie (inscription inside upper cover).
Sold by F. Thomas Heller, Inc. (Swarthmore, Pa.).
Formerly owned by John D. Stanitz (Cleveland, Ohio), Ms. 50.
Acquired by Lawrence J. Schoenberg with other Stanitz manuscripts, Sept. 1997.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2012.
